title: High School Sports Round-up: Soccer, Volleyball, Cross Country
text: Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 3:24 PM Posted Oct. 9, 2015 at 3:24 PM Boy’s Soccer Penn Yan 2 Mynderse 1 The Penn Yan Mustang boy's soccer team squared off against Finger Lakes East rival Mynderse Thursday evening in Penn Yan. The Orange and Blue scored a goal in each half and held off the Blue Devils to pick up a 2-1 win. Scott Fingar scored for Penn Yan in the first half with an assist from Tate Stewart. Noah Hullings added the Mustang's second marker in the second half with Scott Fingar providing a helper. Jon McKay picked up the win for Penn Yan in the nets making 9 saves. With the win, Penn Yan improves its FL East record to 7-3-0. they are 9-4-0 overall. HAC 1 Marcus Whitman 0 Honeoye 1 Marcus Whitman 0 The Marcus Whitman Wildcat boy's soccer dropped two games in Finger Lakes West action. Marcus Whitman's defense played well in both games allowing only one goal in each contest. But the Whitman offense went scoreless in both game. The Wildcats were shutout 1-0 by H.A.C. on Monday (10/5) in Brighton. Two days later, the Whitman boy's once again were shutout by the Honeoye Bulldogs 1-0 at home. Tim Cornish recorded 13 saves in goal for the Wildcats. Marcus Whitman falls to 1-9 in the Finger Lakes West. They are 2-12 overall. Arkport/Canasaraga 2 Dundee/Bradford 1 The combined Dundee/Bradford boy's soccer team was defeated by Arkport/Canasaraga 2-1 Thursday afternoon (10/8). Nick Bailey scored the lone Scotsmen goal. Yannick Wohlhauser picked up an assist. Dundee/Bradford is 3-4-0 in the Steuben Div.II League and 8-6-1 overall. Girl’s Soccer Penn Yan 6 Honeoye 1 The Penn Yan Mustang girl's soccer team defeated Honeoye 6-1 at Mustang Field Monday (10/5). Sabrena Parsons tallied 2 goals in the first half for Penn Yan. Sydney Gifford added a goal and an assist. Anessa Sherman, Cassie Lafler, and Emily Finger also scored goals for Penn Yan. Melanie Gleason recorded 1 save in the nets for the Mustangs. The Orange improved their overall record to 7-5 with the win. HAC 3 Marcus Whitman 1 The Marcus Whitman Wildcat girl's soccer team dropped a 3-1 decision to the Wolves of HAC in Brighton on Monday afternoon (10/5). Emily Thompson scored the Whitman goal with an assist from Courtney Royston. The Wildcats are 3-8 in finger Lakes West action. Dundee/Bradford 4 Romulus 1 The Dundee Scot girl's soccer team downed Romulus 4-1 in a Finger Lakes West contest on Monday afternoon (10/5) in Dundee. The Dundee offense was handled by one person, Tayler Morrison. She scored all four Dundee goals to propel the Scots to the league win (4-7, 2-5). Andi Wood made 6 saves in goal for the Scots. Page 2 of 3 - Volleyball Penn Yan 3 Wayne 1 The Penn Yan Mustang girl's volleyball team traveled to Wayne to take on the first place Eagles in a Finger Lakes East showdown on Wednesday. The high flying Eagles entered the match with a perfect 9-0 record a top the Finger Lakes East standings. The Mustangs were in third place in the league with a 5-2 record. The Yates County girls were more than up to the task of upsetting the first place Wayne team. The two teams played to a 25-25 draw in the first match. Wayne rebounded to take the second game 25-21. But the upstart Mustang were undaunted. They stormed back to take the next two games 25-17 and 25-22 to take the match and hand Wayne their first league loss of the season. Penn Yan improved their league mark to 6-2 with the win. It was a total team effort for sure. For Penn Yan, Emily Wunder led the way with 17 kills, 3 blocks, and 21 digs. Kelly Bray added 25 assists, 8 digs, and served up 2 aces. Jessica Covell contributed 17 digs while teammate Brie Yonge recorded 23 digs and 4 aces in the win. Sydney Bloom delivered 8 kills, 13 digs, and served 2 aces also for Penn Yan. Penn Yan 3 Pal-Mac 0 Earlier in the week in Penn Yan, the Mustangs shutout Pal-Mac 3-0 to earn their 5th Finger Lakes East win. Jessica Covell led the Mustang charge with 11 digs, two kills, and also served up an ace. Kelly Bray added 16 assists and 2 aces. Brie Yonge chipped in 7 digs while Jess Decker added 6 kills, 3 blocks, and 3 aces. Honeoye 3 Dundee 0 The Dundee Scots volleyball team dropped a 3-0 decision to Honeoye in Dundee on Tuesday afternoon (10/6). Jeanetta Jayne delivered 1 kill and 1 dig for the Scots. Dundee falls to 0-10 overall and 0-5 in the Finger Lakes West. Cross Country The Penn Yan Mustang and Marcus Whitman harriers competed in multi-school meets Tuesday afternoon. The Mustangs traveled to Ontario County Park to compete with teams from Honeoye, Clyde-Savannah, HAC, and North Rose-Wolcott. In the boy's meet, the Mustangs defeated HAC 26-29 and North Rose -Wolcott 20-39 and lost to Honeoye 15-50. They are 4-9 in the Wayne Finger Lakes East. Penn Yan's Peyton Silliman finished in 10th place. On the girl's side, Penn Yan defeated NR-W 26-29 but lost to HAC 19-44, Honeoye 20-41, and Clyde-Savannah 23-32. The Mustang girl's team 6-7 in W-FL East League. Macy Nicholson garnered a 4th place finish for the Mustangs. The Marcus Whitman Wildcat teams traveled to Midlakes to compete against Bloomfield and host Midlakes. the Wildcat boy's swept Bloomfield 16-44 and Midlakes 15-44. Gabe Stash, Nate Mayton, Stephen Borsiuk, and Tyler Schwarz finished 1 through 4 for Whitman. Hunter Orbaker came in 6th place. Whitman is in first place in the Wayne -Finger Lakes Central with a 11-1 record. Page 3 of 3 - The MW girl's team lost to Bloomfield 18-38 and Midlakes 15-50. Amanda Cline was Whitman's top finisher in 12th place. The Wildcat girl's record now stands at 0- 11 in the W/FL Central. The Chronicle Express
